<p>Let me introduce myself. Hi! I'm M.Jean.Felix a Haitian-American writer and artist from Boston. I'm an Edie Winsdor Scholar thro Lesbian Who Tech and this is my first fully running site. Its not perfect but its a great start for someone who had only known Ruby for a few short days.</p>
<p>I'm currently attending the General assembly WDI Immersive boot camp, which is incredibly challenging.</p>

<p>I have written a novel called 'Seven Days in Port-au-Prince about my family's experience during the earthquake that devasted Haiti in 2010, an exceprt of which appears in the Lambda literary Foundation anthology Emerge. You can purchase a copy of it at this link.

