<p>After the earthquake that struck Haiti in 2010 I was asked to join the 2nd Ghetto Biennale: A Salon de Refuse, where I performed a piece that was a meditation on the Haitian Diaspora. I gathered items from the debris around Port-au-Prince and created a human figure, which I carried on my back walking the full distance from where my mother was from, Jacmel, to where my father is from Port-au-Prince. It is a distance of 72 kilometers hiking through the mountains. Here is a link to that project.
<%= link_to "2nd Ghetto Biennale: A Salon de Refuse", "http://www.yoonsoo.com/ghetto/files/archive-files/melitza.html" %></br>

<p>I received an M.F.A. in Creative Writing and the novel 'Seven Days in Port-au-Prince was my thesis project. Here is a link to my thesis reading</p>
